content.description:
This has thoughtful climbing on positive holds.

P1. 5.11a. Follow bolts angling up and right along an arete passing several small roofs to anchors shared with

Prickly Pair Left

.
content.location:
This is the fourth bolted route from the left. It shares its start with

Prickly Pair Left

.

content.description:
This has nice face climbing.

P1. 5.10d/11a. Head straight up, and angle a bit left then back right under an overlap to anchors shared with

Prickly Pair Right

.
content.location:
This is the third bolted route from the left sharing a start with

Prickly Pair Right

.

content.description:
Climb the green slab starting with thin face followed by jugs.

P1. 5.11a. Angle up and right through somewhat friable rock to an overlap then straight up on juggy holds to the anchors shared with

Ocatillo

.
content.location: This is the leftmost route on the wall.

content.description:
Thoughtful face on the lower half leads to juggy face to the anchors.

P1. 5.10c. Head up on a tricky face to a seam. Follow the seam to an overlap, then finish up on juggy face shared with

Palo Verde

.
content.location: It is the second route from the left.

content.description: P1. 5.11a. Start in a large corner capped with a roof, step right around the roof, then move up and right to the crux tiered overhang which has some friable rock. Turn the overhang, and continue up passing a couple thin sections to the anchors.
content.protection: Nine bolts to chains.  Take a couple long slings.
content.location: This is the fifth route from the left, just right of a long, right-facing corner.
